    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="661"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.932/10–3148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 5, 1948—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1550. Dept believes Treaty Department revision para. 2 (Embtel 2046, Oct. 31)
                    undesirable because (1) appears continue Art XI partially <pb facs="0782"
                        n="772" xml:id="pg_772"/> in force (2) neglects Senate intention regarding
                    further negotiations (3) paraphrasing risky in any event. Proposed amendment
                    para. 3 protocol exchange ratifications FCN treaty (Embtel 2054, Nov. 1)
                    acceptable. Instrument ratification being prepared. Will be forwarded
                    soonest.</p>
                <p>Dept strongly prefers exchange notes GATT, ITO, Trust Territory either
                    simultaneously with or before exchange ratifications treaty. However, if ForMin
                    unwilling, Emb authorized agree procedure suggested Treaty Department (Embtel
                    2046, Oct. 31).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
